# .trivyignore — accepted / false-positive CVE findings with justification.
# Each entry must include a justification comment explaining the risk acceptance.
# Regenerate with: trivy image --severity CRITICAL --ignore-unfixed <image>

# CVE-2026-22184: zlib CRITICAL in nginxinc/nginx-unprivileged:1.29-alpine (installed: 1.3.1-r2, fixed: 1.3.2-r0)
# Justification: Fix exists in Alpine package repo but nginx-unprivileged image has not yet been
# rebuilt with updated packages. The container serves only static files with no user-supplied
# compressed input; zlib is only used internally by nginx for gzip responses.
# Track: update Dockerfile once nginx-unprivileged is rebuilt with zlib 1.3.2-r0.
CVE-2026-22184
